[SN]TITLE[SN]
Vehicle crashes into side of house on A90 near Portlethen

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Motorists and a homeowner escaped serious injury after a people carrier crashed into a house on the A90 south of Aberdeen.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The people carrier and a lorry left the dual carriageway at Hillside on Thursday morning.
The first vehicle crashed into a house, with the lorry stopping just short of a building.
The homeowner, Jim Cardno, told BBC Scotland he was awoken by an "almighty bang".
